    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-10T20:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-10T20:34:00-05:00" n="572"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2199: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-11T10:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1921—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In connection with my cipher telegram August 10, 10 a.m., through Tokyo<note
                        n="33" xml:id="d572fn33">See telegram no. 272, Aug. 11, from the Chargé in
                        Japan, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> in regard to the loan, following conditions must obtain:</p>
                <p>1st. Technical Board must have control over all receipts and expenditures. 2d.
                    Proceeds of loan to be placed in the hands of Board which shall have sole charge
                    of expenditure for the benefit of railway in its judgment. 3d. Other than
                    members of Board, no person shall be retained in the service of railway in
                    opposition to determinations of that nature [<hi rend="italic">Board</hi>]. The
                    last condition is to prevent the Chinese from loading payroll with high
                    positions for their men as they are now doing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
